                <note rend="inline" type="source">816.01/19: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Guatemala</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Whitehouse</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Guatemala</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-12-14T16:00:00-07:00"
                            >December 14, 1931—4 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 6:16 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>71. Minister of Foreign Affairs has just informed me that Doctor José Victor
                    Gonzales has come to Guatemala on an official mission from the Salvadoran
                    Government to request Guatemala to grant recognition of the new regime and to
                    state what conditions it would impose.</p>
                <p>The Minister replied that he must have time for reflection as Guatemala intended
                    to be guided entirely by the letter and spirit of the treaties.</p>
                <p>Both the President and the Minister of Foreign Affairs are quite firm on this
                    point particularly as they seem to expect trouble in Honduras at any moment.</p>
                <p>Repeated to Salvador.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Whitehouse</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
